events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 25 points and LeBron James dominated down the stretch as the Los Angeles Lakers closed out a nearly two-week trip with a 107-99 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Road warriors: James, Davis lead Lakers past Hawks 107-99

headlines.description: — Malik Monk had the best scoring game of his career, and the Charlotte Hornets got a comeback they won’t soon forget.
headlines.shortLinkText: Monk runs wild, scores 36 as Hornets top Heat 129-121 in OT

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 26 points and Jarrett Allen had 23 points and 18 rebounds, leading the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 100-98 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves and a split of their home-and-home series on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton scores 26 points, Cavaliers edge Timberwolves 100-98

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 30 points, Zach LaVine added 17 of his 21 in the second half and the Chicago Bulls beat the New York Knicks 110-102 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen, LaVine lead way as Bulls beat Knicks 110-102

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday scored 22 points, Bobby Portis added 21 and the Milwaukee Bucks snapped a two-game skid by trouncing the Portland Trail Blazers 134-106 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks sizzle from 3-point range to blast Blazers 134-106

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 38 points, including 17 straight Sacramento points during the final seven minutes, and the Kings erased a 10-point, fourth-quarter deficit for a 118-109 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox's 4th-quarter outburst lead Kings past Pelicans, 118-109

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Eric Gordon scored 25 points and the Houston Rockets hit an NBA record-tying 11 3-pointers in a 48-point first quarter, cruising to a 136-106 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets hit 11 3s in 48-point first quarter, rout Thunder

headlines.description: — Devin Booker hit a 3-pointer with 1.5 seconds left in his first game since Jan. 22 and the Phoenix Suns rallied past the Dallas Mavericks for the second straight game, winning 109-108 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker hits winning 3 in return as Suns edge Mav 109-108

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Gorgui Dieng scored 19 points, Brandon Clarke had 18 and the Memphis Grizzlies routed the San Antonio Spurs 133-102 on Monday night to extend their winning streak to seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies dominate Spurs 133-102 for 7th straight victory
